2 counseling, family behavior therapy, motivational incentives, and other modalities.
3 11. "Policy" means a health benefit plan as defined in section 26.1 - 36.3 - 01 or a denta l
4 benefit plan as defined in section 26.1 - 36.9 - 01. The te rm does not include medica l
5 assistance or the public employees retirement system uniform group insurance
6 program plans under chapter 54 - 52.1 .
7 12. "Prior authorization" means the review conducted before the delivery of a health care
8 service, including an outpatient health care service, to evaluate the necessity,
9 appropriateness, and efficacy of the use of health care services, procedures, and
10 facilities, by a person other than the attending health care professional, for the
11 purpose of determining the medical necessity of the health care services or admission.
12 The term includes a review conducted after the admission of the enrollee and in
13 situations in which the enrollee is unconscious or otherwise unable to provide advance
14 notification. The term does not include a referral or participation in a referral process
15 by a participating provider unless the provider is acting as a prior authorization review
16 organization.
17 13. "Prior authorization review organization" means a person that performs prior
18 authorization for:
19 a. An employer with employees in the state who are covered under a policy;
20 b. An insurer that writes policies;
21 c. A preferred provider organization or health maintenance organization; or
22 d. Any other person that provides, offers to provide, or administers hospital,
23 outpatient, medical, prescription drug, or other health benefits to an individual
24 treated by a health care professional in the state under a policy.
25 14. "Urgent health care service" means a health care service for which, in the opinion of a
26 health care professional with knowledge of the enrollee's medical condition, the
27 application of the time periods for making a non-expedited prior authorization might:
28 a. Jeopardize the life or health of the enrollee or the ability of the enrollee to regain
29 maximum function; or
30 b. Subject the enrollee to pain that cannot be managed adequately without the care
31 or treatment that is the subject of the prior authorization review.
