1 c. Must be knowledgeable of, and have experience providing, the health care
2 services under appeal;
3 d. May not be employed by a prior authorization review organization or be under
4 contract with a prior authorization review organization other than to participate in
5 one or more of the prior authorization review organization's health care provider
6 networks or to perform reviews of appeals, or otherwise have any financial
7 interest in the outcome of the appeal;
8 e. May not have been directly involved in making the adverse determination; and
9 f. Shall consider all known clinical aspects of the health care service under review,
10 including a review of all pertinent medical records provided to the prior
11 authorization review organization by the enrollee's health care provider, any
12 relevant records provided to the prior authorization review organization by a
13 health care facility, and any medical literature provided to the prior authorization
14 review organization by the health care provider.
15 2. A review of an adverse determination involving a prescription drug must be conducted
16 by a licensed pharmacist or physician who is competent to evaluate the specific
17 clinical issues presented in the review.
18 26.1 - 36.12 - 05. Prior authorization - Nonurgent circumstances .
19 1. If a prior authorization review organization requires prior authorization of a health care
20 service, the prior authorization review organization shall make a prior authorization or
21 adverse determination and notify the enrollee and the enrollee's health care provider
22 of the decision within seven calendar days of obtaining all necessary information to
23 make the decision. For purposes of this subsection, "necessary information" includes
24 the results of any face-to-face clinical evaluation or second opinion that may be
25 required.
26 2. A prior authorization review organization shall allow an enrollee and the enrollee's
27 health care provider fourteen business days following a nonurgent circumstance or
28 provision of health care services for the enrollee or health care provider to notify the
29 prior authorization review organization of the nonurgent circumstance or provision of
30 health care services.
