1 26.1 - 36.12 - 06. Prior authorization - Urgent health care services .
2 A prior authorization review organization shall render a prior authorization or adverse
3 determination concerning urgent health care services and notify the enrollee and the enrollee's
4 health care provider of that prior authorization or adverse determination within seventy - two
5 hours after receiving all information needed to complete the review of the requested health care
6 services.
7 26.1 - 36.12 - 07. Prior authorization - Emergency medical condition .
8 1. A prior authorization review organization may not require prior authorization for
9 prehospital transportation or for the provision of emergency health care services for an
10 emergency medical condition.
11 2. A prior authorization review organization shall allow an enrollee and the enrollee's
12 health care provider a minimum of two business days following an emergency
13 admission or provision of emergency health care services for an emergency medical
14 condition for the enrollee or health care provider to notify the prior authorization review
15 organization of the admission or provision of health care services.
16 3. The medical necessity or appropriateness of emergency health care services for an
17 emergency medical condition may not be based on whether those services were
18 provided by participating or nonparticipating providers.
19 4. If an enrollee receives an emergency health care service that requires immediate
20 postevaluation or poststabilization services, a prior authorization review organization
21 shall make an authorization determination within two business days of receiving a
22 request. If the authorization determination is not made within two business days, the
23 services must be deemed approved.
24 26.1 - 36.12 - 08. No prior authorization for medication assisted treatment .
25 A prior authorization review organization may not require prior authorization for the
26 provision of medication assisted treatment for the treatment of opioid use disorder.
27 26.1 - 36.12 - 09. Retrospective denial .
28 A prior authorization review organization may not revoke, limit, condition, or restrict a prior
29 authorization if care is provided within forty-five business days from the date the health care
30 provider received the prior authorization unless there is evidence the prior authorization was
31 based on fraud.
