1 26.1 - 36.12 - 10. Length of prior authorization .
2 A prior authorization is valid for six months after the date the health care provider receives
3 the prior authorization.
4 26.1 - 36.12 - 11. Chronic or long-term care conditions .
5 If a prior authorization review organization requires a prior authorization for a health care
6 service for the treatment of a chronic or long-term care condition, the prior authorization
7 remains valid for twelve months.
8 26.1 - 36.12 - 12. Continuity of care for enrollees .
9 1. On receipt of information documenting a prior authorization from the enrollee or from
10 the enrollee's health care provider, a prior authorization review organization shall
11 honor a prior authorization granted to an enrollee from a previous prior authorization
12 review organization for at least the initial sixty days of an enrollee's coverage under a
13 new policy.
14 2. During the time period described in subsection 1, a prior authorization review
15 organization may perform its review to grant a prior authorization.
16 3. If there is a change in coverage of, or approval criteria for, a previously authorized
17 health care service, the change in coverage or approval criteria does not affect an
18 enrollee who received prior authorization before the effective date of the change for
19 the remainder of the enrollee's plan year. This subsection does not apply if a prior
20 authorization review organization changes coverage terms for a drug or device that
21 has been:
22 a. Deemed unsafe by the United States food and drug administration; or
23 b. Withdrawn by the United States food and drug administration or product
24 manufacturer.
25 4. A prior authorization review organization shall continue to honor a prior authorization
26 the organization has granted to an enrollee if the enrollee changes products under the
27 same health insurance company.
28 26.1 - 36.12 - 13. Failure to comply - Services deemed authorized .
29 If a prior authorization review organization fails to comply with the deadlines and other
30 requirements in this chapter, any health care services subject to review automatically are
31 deemed authorized by the prior authorization review organization.
