1 26.1 - 36.12 - 14. Procedures for appeals of adverse determinations .
2 1. A prior authorization review organization shall have written procedures for appeals of
3 adverse determinations. The right to appeal must be available to the enrollee and the
4 attending health care professional.
5 2. The enrollee may review the information relied on in the course of the appeal, present
6 evidence and testimony as part of the appeals process, and receive continued
7 coverage pending the outcome of the appeals process.
8 26.1 - 36.12 - 15. Effect of change in prior authorization clinical criteria .
9 1. If, during a plan year, a prior authorization review organization changes coverage
10 terms for a health care service or the clinical criteria used to conduct prior
11 authorizations for a health care service, the change in coverage terms or in clinical
12 criteria does not apply until the next plan year for any enrollee who received prior
13 authorization for a health care service using the coverage terms or clinical criteria in
14 effect before the effective date of the change.
15 2. This section does not apply if a prior authorization review organization changes
16 coverage terms for a drug or device that has been:
17 a. Deemed unsafe by the United States food and drug administration; or
18 b. Withdrawn by the United States food and drug administration or product
19 manufacturer.
20 26.1 - 36.12 - 16. Notification to claims administrator .
21 If the prior authorization review organization and the claims administrator are separate
22 entities, the prior authorization review organization shall notify, either electronically or in writing,
23 the appropriate claims administrator for the health benefit plan of any adverse determination
24 that is reversed on appeal.
25 26.1 - 36.12 - 17. Annual report to insurance commissioner .
26 1. A prior authorization review organization shall report to the insurance commissioner by
27 September first of each year information regarding prior authorization requests for the
28 previous calendar year.
29 2. The report must be available online and in a form specified by the commissioner.
30 3. The report must include the:
31 a. Total number of prior authorization requests received;
