16 SECTION 2. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - PRIOR AUTHORIZATION
17 REQUIREMENTS IMPOSED BY THE PUBLIC EMPLOYEES RETIREMENT SYSTEM
18 UNIFORM GROUP INSURANCE PROGRAM PLANS - INSURANCE COMMISSIONER DATA
19 COLLECTION AND REPORT TO LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT.
20 1. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying prior
21 authorization requirements imposed by the public employees retirement system
22 uniform group insurance plans under chapter 54-52.1 and the impact on patient care
23 and health care costs.
24 2. The study must include input from stakeholders, including patients, providers, and
25 commercial insurance plans.
26 3. The study must require insurance plans to submit to the insurance commissioner by
27 July 1, 2025, for the immediately preceding calendar year for each commercial
28 product:
29 a. The number of prior authorization requests for which an authorization was
30 issued;
